author: The Sydney Morning Herald
title: StartupWeek Sydney readies for launch
text:
StartupWeek Sydney will include conferences, keynotes and hackathons.
StartupWeek Sydney starts on Friday, and at least 5000 people are expected to attend the more than 50 events planned to celebrate and strengthen the city's thriving tech start-up community.
Running until October 30, the inaugural event will include conferences, keynotes, hackathons, workshops, panels, pitch nights, round tables, debates, exhibitions, tours, networking events, and parties.
"StartupWeek Sydney aims to be more than a series of events, it identifies the current infrastructure available for people interested in startups to find the education, support, connections and funding they need to build their enterprise," StartupWeek national manager Michelle Williams said.
Venues include UNSW, UTS, Stone & Chalk, Town Hall, Parliament House, Fishburners, ATP Innovations, CBA Innovation Lab, Garvan Institute, Tankstream, BlueChilli, and two moving buses.
